Introduction

ONF (pronounced as On and Off) is a six-member boy group under WM Entertainment. Originally with seven members, they debuted on August 2, 2017, with their first mini album "On/Off". The group has two sub-units—On and Off—which are headed by two leaders: Hyojin and Seungjun.

In 2021, all five Korean members enlisted in the military—a rare occurrence in the K-pop industry. After releasing a special album "Storage of ONF" on August 16, 2022, recorded in advance before enlisting, they were then discharged together in June of 2023, coming back with their seventh mini album "Love Effect" on October 4, 2023.
